      "If you run the following script, it will give you that exception:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\n#!/usr/bin/env ruby\r\nrequire 'rethinkdb'\r\nrequire 'eventmachine'\r\ninclude RethinkDB::Shortcuts\r\n\r\nr.connect(:host => 'localhost', :port => 28015, :db => :test).repl\r\n\r\nclass UserHandler < RethinkDB::Handler\r\n  def on_close\r\n    r.table(:table).em_run(UserHandler)\r\n  end\r\nend\r\n\r\nEM.run do\r\n  r.table(:table).em_run(UserHandler)\r\n  raise\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote that having on_close() issuing another query may seem weird, but it's not. Esp. if on_close() resumes another fiber, changing the context."
